cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel criterion based on empirical prediction error and its variance to improve the accuracy of rating prediction tasks in collaborative filtering. It also involves knowledge transfer between different domains, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with recommendation tasks, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) as recommendation systems often involve analyzing text data.
